# ─── Build artefacts ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Local `go build -o bin/railbase` output + `make cross-compile`
# sweep (railbase_<os>_<arch>[.exe]) + goreleaser `dist/` payload.
/bin/
/dist/

# Admin UI bundle output. The production binary embeds via
# `admin/embed.go` which build-tags against the committed copy, so we
# never want a developer-machine bundle leaking into the repo.
/admin/dist/
/admin/node_modules/
/admin/.vite/
/admin/tsconfig.tsbuildinfo
/admin/vite.config.ts.timestamp-*

# ─── Runtime data ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Railbase data directories — gitignored ANYWHERE in the tree, not
# just at the root. Without the leading slash, `bin/dist/pb_data/`
# (created when an operator runs the dist binary from the repo
# without cd'ing elsewhere) is also excluded. Same for any nested
# `pb_hooks/` and the v1.7.39 setup wizard's persisted `.dsn` /
# `.secret` files which live inside the data dir.
pb_data/
pb_hooks/
pb_i18n/
pdf_templates/

# …but the scaffold templates SHIP these dirs as starter content for
# `railbase init` (embed.FS-loaded). Don't strip them out.
!internal/scaffold/templates/**/pb_data/
!internal/scaffold/templates/**/pb_hooks/
!internal/scaffold/templates/**/pb_i18n/
!internal/scaffold/templates/**/pdf_templates/

# Ad-hoc local data dirs operators sometimes drop next to the binary.
/data/
/storage/
/backups/
/exports/

# ─── Go ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.test
*.out
*.prof
*.pprof
coverage.txt
coverage.html
coverage.out
go.work
go.work.sum

# ─── Node / admin tooling ─────────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
.pnpm-store/

# ─── Env / secrets ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Never commit a `.env` — operator-specific DSN + secrets land here.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.pem
*.key
!docs/**/*.pem
!docs/**/*.key

# Audit / session signing key written to `<DataDir>/.audit_seal_key`
# is already covered by pb_data/, but pin the literal name in case a
# future ops doc shows it relative to repo root.
.audit_seal_key

# ─── Logs / scratch ───────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
*.bak
*.tmp
*.swp
*.swo

# ─── IDE / editor ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
.idea/
.vscode/
*.iml
.nvimlog
.history/

# ─── OS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ─── Claude / agent scratch ───────────────────────────────────────
# Per-machine agent caches live under `.claude/`. Plan caches under
# `/Users/<user>/.claude/plans/` are outside the repo already, but
# keep the in-repo dir out too.
.claude/
